<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-12-23T07:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-12-23T07:00:00-05:00" n="346" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d346">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">860D.001/24: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-12-23T15:00:00+03:00">December
                                    23, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received December 23—2:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1769. My 1740, December 17, 1 p.m.<note n="85" xml:id="d346fn85">Not
                                printed.</note> Although the Soviet press has refrained from any
                            direct comment on the election of Ryti as President of Finland, today’s
                            newspapers reproduce what appears to be a full summary of the speech
                            which he is said to have made yesterday including a quotation of the
                            portion concerning the desire of the Finnish people to maintain friendly
                            and good neighborly relations with the Soviet Union as well as with
                            Germany and Sweden. While not conclusive the reproduction of Ryti’s
                            speech would appear to indicate that the Soviet Government is not
                            displeased with the election of Ryti.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Helsinki.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Steinhardt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>